</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF83FFFFFF39197B861DB707" blockId="20.[160,1156,886,1292]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFF39197B8405B184" author="Meurgey F" box="[160,337,886,911]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="298 - 334" refId="ref27229" refString="Meurgey F. 2013. A catalogue of the West Indian dragonflies (Insecta: Odonata). Ann Soc Entomol Fr. 49 (3): 298 - 334. doi: 10.1080 / 00379271.2013.848066." type="journal article" year="2013">Meurgey (2013)</bibRefCitation>
provides a catalogue of the odonates of the Caribbean. For the island of 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF83FFFFFF3919958477B1BA" box="[160,291,920,945]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, adjacent to St. Thomas, 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFDAF19958643B1BA" author="Ramirez A &amp; Maldonado-Benitez N &amp; Mariani-Rios A &amp; Figueroa-Santiago J" box="[566,791,920,945]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="9711" refId="ref28863" refString="Ramirez A, Maldonado-Benitez N, Mariani-Rios A, Figueroa-Santiago J. 2020. Dragonflies and damselflies (Odonata) from Puerto Rico: a checklist with notes on distribution and habitat. PeerJ. 8: e 9711. doi: 10.7717 / peerj. 9711." type="journal article" year="2020">Ram√≠rez et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
provide updated lists of species. 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF83FFFFFF3919B68744B1DF" authority="(Hagen, 1861)" baseAuthorityName="Hagen" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[160,528,955,980]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Erythemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="credula">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF83FFFFFF3919B68431B1DF" box="[160,357,955,980]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Erythemis credula</emphasis>
(Hagen, 1861)
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF83FFFFFC1919B686E8B1DF" box="[896,956,955,980]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and St. Thomas; however, the St. Thomas record is almost certainly an error (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFCCA19D386ADB1FC" author="Donnelly N" box="[851,1017,990,1015]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="7 - 9" refId="ref24517" refString="Donnelly N. 2002. Odonata of St. Thomas and St. John, Virgin Islands. Argia. 14 (1): 7 - 9." type="journal article" year="2002">Donnelly 2002</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF83FFFFFB9619D38423B612" authority="(Hagen, 1861)" baseAuthorityName="Hagen" baseAuthorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Enallagma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="civile">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF83FFFFFB9619D38582B612" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Enallagma civile</emphasis>
(Hagen, 1861)
</taxonomicName>
is known throughout the Greater Antilles, with records in 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF83FFFFFB9A1E0D81D7B612" box="[1027,1155,1024,1049]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
and St. Thomas (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFECE1E2E879DB637" author="Medina Gaud S &amp; Martorell LF" box="[343,713,1059,1084]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="244 - 272" refId="ref27080" refString="Medina Gaud S, Martorell LF. 1974. The Insects of Caja de Muertos Island, Puerto Rico. J Agric Univ Puerto Rico. 58 (2): 244 - 272. doi: 10.46429 / jaupr. v 58 i 2.10684." type="journal article" year="1974">Medina Gaud and Martorell 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFD4D1E2E8684B637" author="Westfall MJ &amp; May ML" box="[724,976,1059,1084]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" refId="ref31704" refString="Westfall MJ, May ML. 1996. Damselflies of North America. Gainseville (USA): Scientific Publishers; p. 424." type="journal volume" year="1996">
Westfall and 
<date id="9C4110A9FF83FFFFFCFD1E2E8684B637" box="[868,976,1059,1084]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" value="1996-05">May 1996</date>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFC451E2E812AB637" author="Donnelly N" box="[988,1150,1059,1084]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="7 - 9" refId="ref24517" refString="Donnelly N. 2002. Odonata of St. Thomas and St. John, Virgin Islands. Argia. 14 (1): 7 - 9." type="journal article" year="2002">Donnelly 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFF391E4B8417B654" author="Meurgey F" box="[160,323,1094,1119]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="298 - 334" refId="ref27229" refString="Meurgey F. 2013. A catalogue of the West Indian dragonflies (Insecta: Odonata). Ann Soc Entomol Fr. 49 (3): 298 - 334. doi: 10.1080 / 00379271.2013.848066." type="journal article" year="2013">Meurgey 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The large 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF83FFFFFE571E4B87BFB654" authority="(Drury, 1773)" baseAuthorityName="Drury" baseAuthorityYear="1773" box="[462,747,1094,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Anax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="junius">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF83FFFFFE571E4B871AB654" box="[462,590,1094,1119]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Anax junius</emphasis>
(Drury, 1773)
</taxonomicName>
was reported from St. Thomas and St. John by 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFEB71E6584E3B68A" author="Klotz EB" box="[302,439,1128,1153]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref26155" refString="Klotz EB. 1932. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: odonata or dragonflies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 14: 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1932">Klotz (1932)</bibRefCitation>
but has not been reported since. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFCC91E658152B68A" author="Donnelly N" box="[848,1030,1128,1153]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="7 - 9" refId="ref24517" refString="Donnelly N. 2002. Odonata of St. Thomas and St. John, Virgin Islands. Argia. 14 (1): 7 - 9." type="journal article" year="2002">Donnelly (2002)</bibRefCitation>
reports or compiles records of 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF83FFFFFE101E868667B6AF" authority="(Burmeister, 1839)" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[393,819,1163,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Dythemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufinervis">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF83FFFFFE101E86870EB6AF" box="[393,602,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Dythemis rufinervis</emphasis>
(Burmeister, 1839)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF83FFFFFCD91E8685B5B6CC" authority="(Fabricius, 1798)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Pantala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF83FFFFFCD91E86815EB6AF" box="[832,1034,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Pantala flavescens</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1798)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF83FFFFFE871EA3870DB6CC" authority="Hagen, 1861" authorityName="Hagen" authorityYear="1861" box="[286,601,1198,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Tramea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onusta">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF83FFFFFE871EA38497B6CC" box="[286,451,1198,1223]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Tramea onusta</emphasis>
Hagen, 1861
</taxonomicName>
from St. Thomas and St. John. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFC251EA38116B6CC" author="Klotz EB" box="[956,1090,1198,1223]" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref26155" refString="Klotz EB. 1932. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: odonata or dragonflies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 14: 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1932">Klotz (1932)</bibRefCitation>
gives records of 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF83FFFFFE8F1EDD8742B6E2" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1857" box="[278,534,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Erythrodiplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="justiniana">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF83FFFFFE8F1EDD8742B6E2" box="[278,534,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Erythrodiplax justiniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Selys in Sagra, 1857) from St. Thomas, and 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF83FFFFFC641EDD85B2B707" author="Whitehouse FC" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" pagination="199 - 202" refId="ref31729" refString="Whitehouse FC. 1939. Notes on some tropical dragonflies. Can Entomol. 71 (9): 199 - 202. doi: 10.4039 / Ent 71199 - 9." type="journal article" year="1939">Whitehouse (1939)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF83FFFFFECE1EFE87F1B707" authority="(Say, 1840)" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[343,677,1267,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Pantala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="819" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hymenaea">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF83FFFFFECE1EFE8770B707" box="[343,548,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="819">Pantala hymenaea</emphasis>
(Say, 1840)
</taxonomicName>
from St. John.
</paragraph>
